WEBVTT

00:08.220 --> 00:12.240
Hi there, welcome to
this video. Today we

00:12.240 --> 00:14.520
will learn what a
digital footprint is.

00:14.520 --> 00:17.060
A digital footprint
is the trail of data

00:17.060 --> 00:19.680
you leave behind when
you go online.

00:20.100 --> 00:22.020
Understanding
footprints helps you

00:22.020 --> 00:24.520
protect your privacy.
The goal of this

00:24.520 --> 00:26.400
video is to explain
how digital

00:26.400 --> 00:28.480
footprints are
created and why they

00:28.480 --> 00:31.300
matter. We will look
at actions that leave

00:31.300 --> 00:33.640
traces, including
actions you choose

00:33.640 --> 00:35.180
and actions that
happen in the

00:35.180 --> 00:38.300
background. Then we
will practice ways to

00:38.300 --> 00:39.880
leave a smaller
footprint.

00:45.160 --> 00:47.160
Imagine walking on a
beach and leaving

00:47.160 --> 00:50.520
footprints in the
sand. Online, you can

00:50.520 --> 00:52.400
also leave footprints
, but you cannot

00:52.400 --> 00:55.760
always see them. Your
digital footprint is

00:55.760 --> 00:58.420
made from your clicks
, taps and choices.

00:59.240 --> 01:01.980
Some footprints are
created on purpose.

01:01.980 --> 01:04.440
For example, posting
a photo, writing a

01:04.440 --> 01:06.900
comment, liking a
video or sharing a

01:06.900 --> 01:09.560
message. These
actions can be seen

01:09.560 --> 01:11.540
by other people
depending on your

01:11.540 --> 01:14.060
settings. Other
footprints are

01:14.060 --> 01:16.160
created quietly in
the background.

01:16.860 --> 01:19.320
Websites and apps can
record what you click

01:19.320 --> 01:21.780
, how long you stay
on a page and what

01:21.780 --> 01:24.820
you search for. This
can happen even if

01:24.820 --> 01:28.020
you never post
anything. Things that

01:28.020 --> 01:29.700
can be tracked
include pages you

01:29.700 --> 01:31.760
visit, buttons you
press, your device

01:31.760 --> 01:34.980
type and sometimes
your location. Apps

01:34.980 --> 01:37.200
may also track which
videos you watch and

01:37.200 --> 01:40.160
what you buy or look
at. This data helps

01:40.160 --> 01:42.340
services learn what
you might do next.

01:42.980 --> 01:45.020
Many companies track
footprints to

01:45.020 --> 01:47.640
personalize content.
They may show adverts

01:47.640 --> 01:49.240
based on what you
watched or searched

01:49.240 --> 01:52.500
for. They may also
suggest games, videos

01:52.500 --> 01:54.920
or products they
think you will like.

01:58.280 --> 02:00.440
Footprints matter
because data can last

02:00.440 --> 02:03.340
a long time. If too
much data is

02:03.340 --> 02:05.580
collected, it can
reveal patterns about

02:05.580 --> 02:08.620
you, your interests,
routines and habits.

02:08.840 --> 02:11.380
The more data that
exists, the more

02:11.380 --> 02:14.840
careful you need to
be. Oversharing makes

02:14.840 --> 02:17.680
footprints bigger.
Sharing your name,

02:17.680 --> 02:19.900
school or location
can make it easier

02:19.900 --> 02:22.960
for strangers to
identify you. Even

02:22.960 --> 02:25.140
photos can reveal
private details in

02:25.140 --> 02:27.320
the background, like
a school sign or a

02:27.320 --> 02:30.620
home address. In
class, you will

02:30.620 --> 02:32.740
become a data
detective and follow

02:32.740 --> 02:35.800
a character's day
online. You will look

02:35.800 --> 02:37.820
for moments where
data is shared or

02:37.820 --> 02:40.640
collected. Then you
will identify what

02:40.640 --> 02:42.560
information others
could learn from that

02:42.560 --> 02:47.380
trail. Here are
simple ways to leave

02:47.380 --> 02:50.320
a smaller footprint.
First, share less

02:50.320 --> 02:52.800
personal information,
especially in games

02:52.800 --> 02:55.640
and sign-up forms. If
something is not

02:55.640 --> 02:59.880
needed, do not give
it. Second, log out

02:59.880 --> 03:01.780
when you are finished
, especially on

03:01.780 --> 03:05.980
shared devices. Third
, use privacy

03:05.980 --> 03:08.340
settings like Only
Friends instead of

03:08.340 --> 03:10.940
Public. Privacy
settings are like

03:10.940 --> 03:13.040
doors and curtains
that control who can

03:13.040 --> 03:16.720
see your data. If you
do not understand a

03:16.720 --> 03:18.980
setting, ask a
trusted adult to help

03:18.980 --> 03:21.820
. Trusted adults can
help you check app

03:21.820 --> 03:23.760
permissions and
privacy options.

03:23.860 --> 03:26.520
Asking for help is
part of being a smart

03:26.520 --> 03:28.620
and safe digital
citizen.

03:31.860 --> 03:34.700
Let's recap. A
digital footprint is

03:34.700 --> 03:37.700
the trail of data you
leave online. Some

03:37.700 --> 03:40.480
footprints are active
and some are passive.

03:40.480 --> 03:42.700
Smaller footprints
usually mean better

03:42.700 --> 03:46.360
privacy and more
control. Great work!

03:46.360 --> 03:48.020
In this video, you
learned what a

03:48.020 --> 03:50.480
digital footprint is
and how it is created

03:50.480 --> 03:53.300
. Next, watch the
video about

03:53.300 --> 03:55.220
protecting your
personal data online

03:55.220 --> 03:57.880
to learn simple
actions you can take.

03:58.280 --> 03:59.540
Thank you for
watching!

